text: Tuscolameta Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Tuscolameta is a name derived from the Choctaw language meaning "young warrior". Variant names include "Tuscalameta", "Tuscalamita Creek", "Tushalamita", and "Tuskala Mita Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Leake County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Newton County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Scott County, Mississippi
